data.title: Panzer Stadium
data.text:
"We are thrilled to begin playing in Panzer Stadium in 2019. Panzer Stadium is one of the top lacrosse facilities in the nation and we are excited to experience the electric atmosphere on game day. We are truly grateful to Ken Panzer and all of the generous supporters of this project who have transformed our facility into a one-of-a-kind environment."

Missy Dohertyhead coach of the Penn State women's lacrosse team

"The Panzer Stadium project is symbolic of a passionate and loyal legacy of Penn State lacrosse. The Panzer Stadium project is symbolic of a passionate and loyal legacy of Penn State lacrosse," stated Jeff Tambroni, head coach of the Nittany Lion men's lacrosse team. "We are grateful for the generosity of our alumni, family and friends and humbled by the leadership of our lead donors, Ken Panzer and Jordan Kaplan."
